data.content:
Here are the two files:

**Key design points:**

- **Generic** — `@typeparam TItem` lets it work with any item type.
- **Immutable input** — `OnParametersSet` copies `Items` into a private `_items` list, so the parent's collection is never mutated.
- **Events flow up** — after each swap, `OnOrderChanged` fires with a read-only snapshot of the reordered list.
- **`@key`** on each `<li>` ensures efficient DOM diffing during reorders.
- **Buttons disable** at boundaries (first item can't move up, last can't move down).

**Usage** (as you described):

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = [ /* ... */ ];

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
